NAME
hsh - a simple shell program

SYNOPSIS
./hsh

DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple shell program that can execute commands entered by the user or read from a file or pipeline.

vbnet
Copy code
   Unless specified otherwise, the output of hsh must be exactly the same as the output of the sh (/bin/sh) shell, as well as the exact same error output. The only difference is when hsh prints an error, the name of the program must be equivalent to your argv[0].
USAGE
To run hsh in interactive mode, simply execute the program without any arguments:

vbnet
Copy code
          $ ./hsh
          ($)

   hsh will display a prompt consisting of a dollar sign ($), indicating that it is ready to accept commands. Enter the command you wish to execute, and press Enter to execute it.

   To exit the shell, type "exit" and press Enter:

          ($) exit
          $

   To run hsh in non-interactive mode, pipe a file or a pipeline into hsh:

          $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
          hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

   hsh will execute the commands in the file or pipeline and display the output.
