COMPILATION
hsh can be compiled using the following command:

          gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh
EXAMPLES
Execute a command in interactive mode:

bash
          $ ./hsh
          ($)
          ($) /bin/ls
          hsh main.c shell.c
          ($)
          ($) exit
          $

   Execute a command in non-interactive mode:

          $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
          hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

   Execute commands from a file in non-interactive mode:

          $ cat test_ls_2
          /bin/ls
          /bin/ls
          $ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
          hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
          hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
